Finder Toggle Hidden Files Service
==================================
Simple bash-script based service that toggles the visibility of hidden files in Finder


Installation
------------
* Double click the .workfow file. Automator will open.
* Click 'Install' to install the service.
* Open a Finder window.
* Go to menu Finder -> Services -> Toggle Hidden Files

Create Command + Shift + Period (.) keyboard shortcut
-----------------------------------------------------
* Open System Preferences -> Keyboard -> Services
* Scroll down to General
* Double click on the most right end of the Toggle Hidden Files table row
* Set the keyboard shortcut by pressing Command + Shift + Period (.)